{"questionId":"17549","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chicken eggs are classified by grade (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>7</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>), based on weight. A mixed carton&nbsp;contains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn></math> eggs and could include eggs from any grade. As part of the science project,&nbsp;Rocky buys <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math> mixed cartons and sorts the eggs according to their weight.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5adc2e64419163c2f6e1801e331715c92cf4b719.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the modal grade of the eggs.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;(C1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A0)</strong></em> for an answer of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>w</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>70</mn></math>.</span></p>\n<p><em><strong><span class=\"mjpage\">[1 mark]</span></strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17549","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.T_13b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the modal grade of the eggs.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}